tool_description: OnePost is social media management infrastructure for the internet. Companies use our API to create, post, and manage their social presence via programmatic communication. You can think of it like a headless Hootsuite built for developers.
title: OnePost

api_list.name: Get a Provider
api_list.description: Get data for a single Provider record

api_list.name: Get All Providers
api_list.description: Returns all Provider records owned by the API user account.

api_list.name: Get an Authorization
api_list.description: Returns data for a single Authorization

api_list.name: Get All Authorizations
api_list.description: Return all authorizations belonging to all Providers.

api_list.name: Get All Social Posts
api_list.description: Get all SocialPosts owned by the API user

api_list.name: Get a Social Post
api_list.description: Get data for a single SocialPost owned by the API user

api_list.name: Create an Authorization
api_list.description: Authorization creation must be done through a web browser. This endpoint provides a URL where you can create a new Authorization (along with some instructions). In a Production environment, your users would simply click on a link to create these Authorization records.

api_list.name: Delete an Authorization
api_list.description: Immediately deletes an Authorization record. **WARNING:** This will remove all data belonging to the Authorization, such as SocialPost records.

api_list.name: Get an Authorized Page
api_list.description: Gets data for a single AuthorizedPage record

api_list.name: Get All Authorized Pages
api_list.description: Returns all AuthorizedPage records owned by the API user

api_list.name: Get All Posts
api_list.description: Get all posts that have been created by the API user.

api_list.name: Publish a Post
api_list.description: Publish a post so that the content is sent to the social networks (specified by `authorized_page_ids`). The state of the post will transition from "draft" to "publishing" as each SocialPost attempts to send its content to the AuthorizedPage. Once completed, the Post will have a final state of "published".

api_list.name: Delete a Post
api_list.description: Immediately deletes a single Post in from the OnePost database. **Note:** This only deletes the post from OnePost. OnePost does not currently ever delete content from an AuthorizedPage.

api_list.name: Get a Post
api_list.description: Fetch data for a single Post record owned by the API user

api_list.name: Update a Webhook
api_list.description: Update a webhook endpoint URL for a Webhook owned by the API user

api_list.name: Create a Webhook
api_list.description: Creates a new Webhook for the API user. When an event is created within OnePost, we will attempt to send a POST request with event data for all Webhook endpoints that are registered.

api_list.name: Get a Webhook
api_list.description: Return data for a single Webhook owned by the API user

api_list.name: Delete a Webhook
api_list.description: Deletes a webhook owned by the API user

api_list.name: Get All Webhooks
api_list.description: Return all data for webhooks owned by the API user

api_list.name: Get All Events
api_list.description: Return all event data created on behalf of the API user

api_list.name: Create a Test Event
api_list.description: Creates a test event to test your webhook callback endpoint. When events are created, we will attempt to send the event to all Webhooks owned by the API user.

api_list.name: Get an Event
api_list.description: Return data for a single Event record owned by the API user

api_list.name: Delete a Provider
api_list.description: Remove a Provider record from the system. **Warning:** This will immediately delete all data that belongs to this provider, such as Authorizations.

api_list.name: Update a Provider
api_list.description: Update a single Provider record owned by the API user

api_list.name: Get All Images
api_list.description: List all images that have been uploaded.

api_list.name: Get an Image
api_list.description: Get data for a single Image record

api_list.name: Create an Image
api_list.description: Upload a new image to the image library, which can later be used as a pre-uploaded image option in [OnePost UI](https://github.com/akdarrah/onepost-ui)

api_list.name: Delete an Image
api_list.description: Remove an image record from the library of options

api_list.name: Get a Post Intent
api_list.description: The [OnepostUI Javascript library](https://github.com/akdarrah/onepost-ui) will create Post Intent records rather than a Post directly. This is due to the fact that the UI library uses the `public_key` rather than the `secret_key` to authenticate. Use this endpoint to inspect the Post Intent record before using the [Create a Post endpoint](https://rapidapi.com/onepost/api/onepost1?endpoint=apiendpoint_7cae6f56-d9c9-4d9c-8c6f-51d0feccb598) to create an actual Post record. *Note:* Specifially, it is important to look at the `authorized_page_ids` of the Post Intent to make sure the user actually has access to the IDs requested.

api_list.name: Create a Post
api_list.description:
Creates a new post in the "draft" state. After creating a new post, use the "publish" endpoint to send the post to each AuthorizedPage.

[Upload an image.](https://rapidapi.com/onepost/api/onepost1/tutorials/create-a-post-with-image-upload)

api_list.name: Create a Provider
api_list.description: Create a new Provider record using data obtained by registering a developer application with a provider (such as Twitter or Facebook)

api_list.name: Update an Image
api_list.description: Update the source field for an Image.

api_list.name: Update a Post
api_list.description: Use this endpoint to update a draft post owned by the API user. Once a post has been published, it can no longer be updated.
